    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix missing extract_01_c_rnti function causing undefined behavior\n\n### Summary\nUsers calling the `extract_01_c_rnti()` function were experiencing undefined behavior as this function was not implemented in the codebase. This caused crashes and unpredictable results when attempting to extract C-RNTI from UL MAC CEs.\n\nThis fix implements the missing function with proper C-RNTI extraction according to 3GPP specifications.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_UE/nr_ue_procedures.c`: Added complete implementation of `extract_01_c_rnti()` function\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_UE/mac_proto.h`: Added function declaration\n\n### Reproduction\nPrior to this fix, calling `extract_01_c_rnti()` with a valid UL MAC PDU would result in:\n- Segmentation fault due to missing function implementation\n- Undefined behavior when attempting to extract C-RNTI values from UL MAC CEs\n- Inability to process uplink MAC control elements properly\n\nAfter applying this fix, the function properly:\n- Parses UL MAC PDUs and extracts C-RNTI when present in C-RNTI MAC CEs\n- Handles all UL SCH logical channel identifiers correctly\n- Returns extracted C-RNTI value or 0 if not found/invalid\n- Provides detailed logging for debugging purposes\n\nThe implementation follows 3GPP TS 38.321 section 6.1.3.2 specification for C-RNTI MAC CE format and processing.\n"
}